        <updateDate>2011-10-07T21:48:30Z</updateDate>
        <text><![CDATA[ <p>Storm Shelter Tax Relief Act - Amends the Internal Revenue Code to allow a tax deduction, up to $2,500 in a taxable year, for the cost (including labor)&nbsp;of purchasing, constructing, and installing a qualified storm shelter.&nbsp; Terminates such deduction after 2012.</p> <p>Rescinds unobligated funds from the Community Development Fund authorized by the Department of Housing and Urban Development Appropriations Act, 2010 and the Department of Defense and Full-Year Continuing Appropriations Act, 2011.</p>]]></text>
      </summary>
    </summaries>
